review_id:
A home turned into such a cute cozy coffee shop with delicious coffee. There is limited parking in front and the side of the building. There is a new big parking lot behind the coffee shop that you are able to park at.

Multiple sitting: bar style, couches, table seating, and patio seating.

If you enjoy your coffee there then you get a mug to enjoy it in.

I loved the cafe con leches. No hint of bitter coffee and not sweet. Deliciousness in a cup.

Add this place to your rotation if coffee shops to visit whether it's for me time, study time, socializing, or work time.

review_id:
We ordered lattes, cafe de olla, chicken and corn tamales, marranito (piggy) and empanadas.

Honestly the food was very good.
The latte was delicious. And the marranito tasted well. Some places the marranito is hard or doesn't have flavor. This one tasted recently made.

My only complaint here was the price of the tamales. As a Hispanic person when I saw they charge $10 for ONE tamale I was taken back. I can get half a dozen for the same price that taste amazing.

Either way I ordered two because I'm a sucker for tamales with coffee. And they were good, thankfully. Because if I had paid $20 for two tamales and they tasted back I probably would have asked them for a refund out of principal.

The place is clean and quiet and was filled with millennials studying on their computers (typical heights area ambiance).

Overall I'd come again.

review_id:
Vibe- This is one of the most cozy coffee shops I've been to! Maybe it's because it literally is a house that was turned into a coffee shop :) there's a big space in the front and then there's 3 other rooms with plenty of seating options. There's 3 bar style areas to sit at, some couches, and a great amount of tables with chairs. There's some seating outside too!

Customer service- Amazing! The barista that served me was sweet and helpful.

Food/drinks- I got a cortado with oat milk and vanilla. To eat I got the black bean tamales that came with plantain chips and everything was so good!

Parking- There's about 9 spots in the lot of the shop and then street parking as well.

review_id: Great cozy place. Wonderful spot to study (except for the back ground music, which is sometimes off) and the dim light is very soothing. The staff is just super sweet and amazing. There is a decent number and types of seats to choose from as well; indoors and outdoors. However, the parking can be a hassle as is the case with many other cafes/restaurants in the area. And also the food is really unimpressive. Maybe only on Sundays or that one particular Sunday I was there, starving! The pastries were not fresh (made the previous day according to the cashier) and there was only one choice of food: tamales which was honestly not the best tamales in town. AND it was definitely over-priced. I think I'll go back there but definitely not order food...

review_id:
Definitely a great and spacious place to work and relax in the middle of downtown. Parking was a breeze early morning and I enjoyed my Americano which was absolutely the way I liked it. It was pretty quiet from 7-9 and then started filling in quite quickly.
Quills has an array of spring flavors, baked goods such as muffins and cookies and a variety of coffee beans and apparel to choose from.
The glass panes gives an open vibe and the contemporary furniture gives a very casual and comfortable feel. Quills is dog friendly so overall great place to work out of.

review_id: Coffee is phenomenal. Pastries are decent. Service pulls a great espresso and can make a beautiful latte. My critique is just how elitist and unfriendly the baristas were. I went in with a very chill 3 year old got several drinks and pastries and it was SO unfriendly. It was like I lived in Seattle again! I'll go back for coffee but only if some of the warmer places aren't open. The thing Indiana does well is warmth...even hipsters here tend to be friendly...but not today.

review_id: I was in Indianapolis for the day and stopped by Quill's for a pick-me-up after driving for a few hours. I got a latte and a bag of beans to take home and enjoy. They called me for my drink and without thinking, I left the bag of beans that I had purchased on one of the tables next to the couch. I left the store and did not realize until much later in the day when I was already out of Indy that I had left the beans there. My wife emailed the following day to see if there was anything they could do. She received a response from Jess Magness, General Manager, and they ended up shipping the bag of beans that I purchased along with some stickers. Incredible coffee and customer service!

review_id:
Native Coffee Co. is a small artisanal coffee roastery that has taken the coffee scene by storm with their exceptional espresso offerings. Nestled in the heart of a vibrant urban neighborhood, this family-owned business has developed a loyal following of coffee enthusiasts and connoisseurs.

What sets Native Coffee Co.'s espresso apart is their unwavering commitment to sourcing only the finest coffee beans from indigenous communities worldwide. By forging direct relationships with local farmers, they ensure that their beans are ethically and sustainably cultivated, supporting the livelihoods of those who tend the land. This philosophy not only delivers superior taste but also promotes fair trade and environmental stewardship.

The secret to their delightful espresso lies in the roasting process. Native Coffee Co.'s skilled artisans carefully hand-roast small batches of beans to perfection, achieving a harmonious balance between brightness and depth. The result is a bold and rich flavor profile, with notes of dark chocolate, caramel, and hints of ripe fruit.

Stepping into Native Coffee Co.'s cozy cafe is an immersive experience in itself. The aroma of freshly ground coffee fills the air as baristas expertly craft each cup with precision and passion. Whether you prefer a velvety smooth latte or a simple shot of espresso, their dedication to quality ensures a consistently exceptional coffee experience.

For coffee lovers seeking an ethically-sourced, soulful espresso with a story to tell, Native Coffee Co. stands as a beacon of excellence in the world of specialty coffee.

review_id: If you are only making a small order, like 1 coffee, this Tim's is fine. But whenever you make a slightly bigger order they always mess it up. Usually I just shrug it off and deal with it, but on the odd occasions I go ask for it to be corrected. When/if you do this the staff are incredibly rude and honestly not worth getting their mistakes fixed. The other Tim's in town are better, so if you are wanting better service then go there. Yes I know it's just Tim Hortons, but I still like nice customer service no matter where it is.

review_id: After driving all the way from Calgary I was starving so I stopped here for a quick bite to eat. BIG mistake. Most of the tables were dirty even though the restaurant was empty. The food is disgusting:  Very old, dry, hard, stale chicken patty on the burger. I asked for a slice of tomato to make it more palatable but the children working here were very confused, then finally wanted to charge me after finally understanding I wanted tomato even though it typically doesn't come with one. Fine, but seriously it's a slice of tomato. The soup was so gelatinous I couldn't eat it - thick tasteless goop. And every time I blinked a new bug was attacking my food (see photos). Skip this location at all costs.

I don't know what kind of 'egg product' was used, but it was the worst taste and consistency Ive ever had in an egg. Needless to say, this is the last time I'll visit this place. Do yourself a favor and go to Starbucks across the street.

review_id: Spot Coffee is always an excellent local business choice for leisurely meetups or for a respite.  I do like the food, am not a coffee drinker so cannot comment on that aspect, the atmosphere is very "chill" as the kids say, and I find the barristas professional.  I only dropped a star overall and in the service category as the hours are more limited than the past.  That being said, that is the way of the world as the employment pool has shrunk, wages have rightfully increased, and as Mick Jagger once told me on a record, "You can't always get what you want."  I'm just glad they are open a good amount of the time!

review_id: I've had good espresso drinks from here years ago but their quality has decreased since then. Today, my espresso was under-extracted and the milk was wayyy too hot. I would probably go to Blue Bottle across the street for their consistency in great espresso drinks.
review_text: I've had good espresso drinks from here years ago but their quality has decreased since then. Today, my espresso was under-extracted and the milk was wayyy too hot. I would probably go to Blue Bottle across the street for their consistency in great espresso drinks.
response_from_owner_text:
Hey Charlotte, 

That's sad to hear but we've had the same crew there for the past couple of years but we opted to serve higher quality single original espresso on bar recently, which is noticably less chocolate-y. My wife Liza, the other founder is there every day. It's also sad that it sounds like you have had great drinks and the one day you got a mediocre drink is when we got a not-so-great review from you. Hope you can come by again to give another try, as I'm sure our quality is far higher than Blue Bottle. I am a former BB veteran and know their process well, we are also not owned by Nestle and pay our employees higher .

-Rich

review_id: I bought a tres leches to go from here, and it was stale and tasted bitter. Its ok if the item is not delectable but the least, it shouldn't be stale! Could mess with the gut if i ate more than a bite. :((
review_text: I bought a tres leches to go from here, and it was stale and tasted bitter. Its ok if the item is not delectable but the least, it shouldn't be stale! Could mess with the gut if i ate more than a bite. :((
response_from_owner_text: Hi there, Sorry you didn't enjoy it. It's a pretty popular cake and we make it fresh. There's nothing in the cake that would make it bitter but we do put fresh squeezed orange juice in the cake. Additionally, we also toast the coconut as part of the ingredient. Was there a reason why you chose not to let us know?

review_id:
+1 for environmental friendliness with provision of compostable utensils/containers
+1 for quick prep
+1 friendly staff

However, the presentation was lacking. I was definitely expecting something more exciting out of the smoke & mirrors drink, which ended up being just that - smoke and mirrors. Edible gold dust? Didn't see it in the drink. The sandwich looked pretty vanilla. The taste was also lacking. The pulled pork sandwich tasted more like a school cafeteria sloppy joe (you may be into that but I wasn't). The coffee had an interesting floral flavor but I'm not sure it would really be anyone's "go to" drink. But that's just me.

Would have given 4/5 but the price points at $7 for a drink and $11 for pulled pork sandwich leaves a slight bitter taste in my palate and leaves me feeling that I didn't get the best foodie ROI. Also, not sure I get a lot of experimental "lab" out of the textures/tastes/presentation.

review_id:
I've been to this place a few times.
The danishes are ok. They seem to be sourced locally from someone, maybe cake and bacon? But no worries there they are good.
The coffee is really decent too! I've had no issues with their lattes I've tried.
The one thing I really can't stand and don't get the hype over is the moon milk. It has a very odd flavor. It's often compared to Starbucks sweet cream but in my opinion is no comparison at all. I've read it has several ingredients to make up it's flavor and texture. To me, it just doesn't work and ruins the drink.
The rest is fine tho.

response_from_owner_text: Thank you for providing feedback, Alicia. We in fact do use Cake and Bacon for all of our pastries at our SW Houston locations. We also understand that our moon milk is not for everyone. We do however, also offer a wide variety of traditional lattes and coffees as well. Just ask our baristas the next time you drop by and well gladly make something great for you. We strive for exceptional customer experiences. We'd love to hear more about how we could be a 5-star experience for you. Feel free to reach out to hello@summermoon.com to tell us more.

review_id:
Order: As a first timer, I got the summer moon Java chip blended drink with extra chocolate drizzle inside. The drink was so flavor packed with what was evident that it was made with quality ingredients. It took me no time to devour the drink.

Customer service: The gentleman taking my order recommended a great option tailored to my drink presences. The suggestion turned out to exceed my expectations as the drink was delicious.

Location: I used the drive through to access this location. The drive through was a seemingly quick experience as it was not busy at the time of my visit. There seemed to be lots of parking available.

I would definitely visit this location again!

review_id: This is a nice spot to come to if you need to get some studying done, work done, or just want to catch up with friends over coffee! There's indoor seating, outdoor seating, and also a drive thru. The customer service is good. I got a matcha moon latte on my first visit and I was honestly a little hesitant because I always get just a matcha latte at coffee shops, but this drink turned out to be so delicious. This coffee shop is known for their fire roasted coffee and moon milk that is a "blend of seven secret ingredients- rich, sweet, creamy goodness!" I'll be back for sure!

review_id:
A real local community coffee shop with personality and heart. There's a community bulletin board, food drive bin, and eclectic art referencing music and neighborhoods a Houston "Native" will recognize right away. Plants and chill music give a relaxed vibe. Great place to bring a friend or first date, or to study.  Coffee was very good and service efficient and friendly. Yay! I love supporting a local Houston business.
Don't miss the wonderful historic Gregory School murals and the Historic Freedman's Town marker when in the area. There is a lot of fascinating history in the Fourth Ward.

She made it to order, suggested some food options for next time we come, and even put on some extra love with the Christmas sprinkles. Will definitely come by again to try Moms soup!

review_id:
Coffee: pretty standard coffee, but not bad at all! I got an iced mocha latte and it was good.

Sandwich: these people have extremely unique sandwich options that seem to change frequently. I got The Richmond, and it had toppings like chicken, crispy jalapeno, and green apple slices. I know it sounds weird but it was amazing. 10/10 recommend.

Service: the lady working the counter was friendly and helpful! They seem super nice.
Atmosphere: outside, the seating is beautiful with lots of plants, but it isn't a great place to sit in the peak summer heat. Also, there is a car shop sharing a wall with them, so I heard a lot of drilling and hammering. Their music choice is very much pop top 100, such as passion fruit by drake, sza, etc. Inside, it's pretty dull and grey. There is some nice decor and they have good AC, but other than that it wasn't that cozy.

Overall, it was a 6/10! I would stop by here to grab a lunch or coffee, or maybe sit here on a cooler day.

review_id:
Quaint little coffee shop near Montrose and the fourth ward. It's a little easy to miss while driving as it's in between two other buildings, but look for the large banner (pictured) with Native Coffee logo on the black fence decorated in vines. Parking is also a little tricky. You go slightly past the coffee shop and turn right at the mechanic/body shop. There's free parking in that large parking lot on the right, despite the parking signs threatening to be towed (confirmed by the employee at Native Coffee). Once you walk in, there's a beautiful patio and inside you'll find a clean, small coffee shop that looks newly renovated. The worker was great and I think I might have spotted the owner in the back working on sandwiches. They have a great menu but went basic and got my usual ice vanilla latte. There's roughly 15 tables and plenty of space when I visited. Only downside is that there were only a few outlets I could spot, but not an issue while I was there. Looked like they had a lot of customers from the neighborhood and a few from the car shop.

Definitely check it out!

review_id: Went today for coffee. Had coffee and cinnamon swirl cake. Was very good. Employees were super nice. I was so impressed with how nice this place is. I cant think of a place better kept. It was spotless.  You can see the pride taken by the owners,manager and employess...way to go!

review_id: Stopped in on our way across Texas, They have delicious pastries and solid coffee. The service was also friendly as well

review_id: What a pleasant surprise for a small town coffee shop. Renovations very well done. My Chai tea latte was outstanding. Here for the weekend and will be there every morning. Keep up the good work!
review_text: What a pleasant surprise for a small town coffee shop. Renovations very well done. My Chai tea latte was outstanding. Here for the weekend and will be there every morning. Keep up the good work!
response_from_owner_text: We are very happy that you visited and were pleased with your drink! Hope to see you again very soon.

review_id:
Julee's Mocha is a cute local owned coffee shop and cafe. They offer a variety of coffees and teas, snacks, breakfast and lunch. Located inside the NIA center so next time you need a license renewal stop in and get your coffee from Julee's Mocha.

review_id: Ordered a custom gift set from Julee's Mocha for a client and it was AMAZING! The collection of delicious edibles, great coffee, and adorable goodies came in a box shaped like a book (who doesn't love that?!). Not only was the client delighted, we retained their business for the future AND they were introduced to a new (female-owned, Black-owned) coffee shop that they love! Thanks so much to the Julee's Mocha team!

review_id: The place is very cute in style and the food is pretty good! Will be coming here again. There's a drink called the Bicoff Cookie Latte that's one of my personal favourites.
review_text: The place is very cute in style and the food is pretty good! Will be coming here again. There's a drink called the Bicoff Cookie Latte that's one of my personal favourites.

review_id: It's an awesome thing to see business owners who are passionate about what they do, and step up to serve as industry leaders who help educate others. Ausha is all that and then some! I got the opportunity to attend a coffee conference with her and I can't remember the last time I learned so much while having such a great time. But that's beside the point! What's critical to note is that Ausha knows her stuff when it comes to zoom-zoom juice. That means your coffee-loving taste buds are in the best hands at Julee's Mocha!
